radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung bases demonstrate minimal dependent atelectasis, without consolidation or effusion. Marked periappendiceal fat stranding with dilated appendix to 15 mm, mucosal hyper-enhancement, and a 10 mm appendicolith identified. Additional large fecalith at the base of the cecum. Small fluid collection of 2.6 x 1.4 cm in the right paracolic gutter adjacent to the appendix. No bowel obstruction. Mild-to-moderate degenerative change in the visualized thoracolumbar spine.
